king device is attached to the <span class='question-badge'>35</span> <input type='text' id='ans-35' style='width: 180px; padding: 6px; border: 1px solid #ced6e0; border-radius: 6px; outline: none;'> of the crocodile.</li></ul><h3 style='color: #2f3542; margin-top: 25px; border-left: 4px solid #e84393; padding-left: 10px;'>Relocation of crocodiles:</h3><ul style='list-style-type: none; padding-left: 5px;'><li style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>• 36. Scientists relocate the crocodiles by using a <span class='question-badge'>36</span> <input type='text' id='ans-36' style='width: 180px; padding: 6px; border: 1px solid #ced6e0; border-radius: 6px; outline: none;'>.</li><li style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>• 37. Relocated crocodiles follow the most <span class='question-badge'>37</span> <input type='text' id='ans-37' style='width: 180px; padding: 6px; border: 1px solid #ced6e0; border-radius: 6px; outline: none;'> route home.</li><li style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>• 38. Crocodiles can find their way because they have the ability to <span class='question-badge'>38</span> <input type='text' id='ans-38' style='width: 180px; padding: 6px; border: 1px solid #ced6e0; border-radius: 6px; outline: none;'>.</li></ul><h3 style='color: #2f3542; margin-top: 25px; border-left: 4px solid #e84393; padding-left: 10px;'>Conclusions:</h3><ul style='list-style-type: none; padding-left: 5px;'><li style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>• 39. The crocodiles find their direction by using their senses to the <span class='question-badge'>39</span> <input type='text' id='ans-39' style='width: 180px; padding: 6px; border: 1px solid #ced6e0; border-radius: 6px; outline: none;'>.</li><li style='margin-bottom: 12px;'>• 40. Crocodiles have the same migration system as <span class='question-badge'>40</span> <input type='text' id='ans-40' style='width: 180px; padding: 6px; border: 1px solid #ced6e0; border-radius: 6px; outline: none;'>.</li></ul></div>"
